Finally got it.

On dual-head configurations ddcci_probe() enumerates monitors in order
they appear on i2cbus. I.e. pci:1:0:0-0 goes before pci:1:0:0-1.
However, gdk_screen_get_monitor_at_window() may return 0 as index of
monitor on pci:1:0:0-1. This happens on my dual-head  ATI with
'radeon' driver and MergedFB. Main monitor uses DVI port and has
larger resolution, but DVI port is pci:1:0:0-1. So gddccontrol being
on monitor 0 thinks it's pci:1:0:0-0.

I believe, probe_monitors() should rearrange monitors list to match
GTK's understanding of monitor order. Unfortunately I couldn't find a
way to do this because i've never dealt with xserver or gtk code : (
So I can't help any more  : (

Hope someone may correct this bug.

-- 
Sincerely yours, Arty
[ http://arty.name ]


